# Create an OpenVPN Server on a VPS instance
#
# 1) One User per Server
# 2) Create profiles for:
#   a) Desktop (1x)
#   b) Laptop (1x)
#   c) iPhone (1x)
#   d) Android (1x)
#   d) Table (1x)
# 3) Give access to all 5 devices at the same time
# 4) Turn OFF Server before reaching bandwith CAP ( @ 90 % )
#
# # # # #

# DISABLE SSH ROOT ACCESS
nano /etc/ssh/sshd_config
# search for: #PermitRootLogin
# and replace it with:
PermitRootLogin no

